              "origin": "syntopicon",
              "content": "<p> The <strong>Pact of Brotherhood</strong> (Arabic: <em>‘Aqd al-Mu’ākhāh</em>) refers to a pact or an act of agreement that the Prophet Muḥammad instituted in Medina shortly after the Migration (<em>al-Hijra</em>), which generally--but not always--linked one of the Emigrants (<em>al-Muhājirūn</em>) with one of the Helpers (<em>al-Anṣār</em>) as brothers. Each would rely upon the other as if they were sibling brothers but without the same full legal consequences--such as obligatory rights of inheritance and being intimate family members (<em>maḥārim</em>). Sometimes, however, the brothers did choose to include their brother from the pact in their inheritance, until God revealed the Qur’ānic verse limiting inheritance to actual blood relatives. Sometimes, they were even willing to divorce one of their wives for the other brother to marry. The Pact of Brotherhood sometimes linked the wealthy with the poor, the master with the slave, and those of high tribal standing to those of no standing. Thus, for example, the Prophet’s uncle Ḥamza ibn ‘Abd al-Muṭṭalib al-Muhājir was made the brother of Zayd ibn Ḥārith, who was a former slave and had been the Prophet’s adopted son. </p><p>The Prophet was the brother of al-Imām ‘Alī ibn Abī Ṭālib al-Muhājir</p><p>Abū Bakr al-Ṣiddīq al-Muhājir was made the brother of Khārija ibn Abī Zuhayr al-Anṣārī</p><p>‘Umar ibn al-Khaṭṭāb al-Muhājir was made the brother of ‘Utbān ibn Mālik al-Anṣārī</p><p>‘Uthmān ibn ‘Affān al-Muhājir was made the brother of Aws ibn Thābit al-Anṣārī</p><p>Ja‘far ibn ibn Abī Ṭālib al-Muhājir was made the brother of Mu‘ādh ibn Jabal al-Anṣārī</p><p>Ḥamza ibn ‘Abd al-Muṭṭalib al-Muhājir was made the brother of Zayd ibn Ḥāritha</p><p>‘Abd al-Rahman ibn ‘Awf al-Muhājir was made the brother of Sa‘d ibn Rabī‘ al-Anṣārī</p><p>Ṭalḥa ibn ‘Ubayd-Allāh al-Muhājir was made the brother of Ka‘b ibn Mālik al-Anṣārī</p><p>Muṣ ‘ab ibn ‘Umayr al-Muhājir was made the brother of Abū Ayyūb al-Anṣārī</p><p>‘Ammār ibn Yāsir al-Muhājir was made the brother of Ḥudhayfa ibn al-Yamān al-Anṣārī</p><p>Abū al-Dardā’ al-Anṣārī was made the brother of Salmān al-Fārsī al-Anṣārī</p><p>Manzar ibn ‘Umar was made the brother of Abū Dharr al-Ghifārī</p><p>Abu ‘Ubayda ibn al-Jarrāḥ al-Muhājir was made the brother of Muḥammad ibn Maslama</p><p>Bilāl was made the brother of ‘Ubāda ibn al-Ḥārith</p><p>Al-Zubayr ibn al-‘Awwām al-Muhājir was made the brother of ‘Abd-Allāh ibn Mas‘ūd </p>",
              "sectionId": "book-five-god-s-last-messenger-muhammad-best-known-most-closely-observed-most-successful-of-all-god-s-prophets"
