              "content": "<p> <strong>The Farewell Pilgrimage (<em>Ḥijjat al-Wadā‘</em>)</strong> was performed in the year 10/632 after the peaceful Conquest of Mecca in 8/630 and was the only pilgrimage that the Prophet performed after the beginning of his Mission. The Prophet performed the Farewell Pilgrimage with roughly one hundred thousand of his Companions, who had gathered in Medina and surrounding regions to accompany him on the journey. On the Day of ‘Arafa—the ninth day of the Pilgrimage—the Prophet delivered his famous Farewell Sermon (<em>Khuṭbat al-Wadā‘</em>). </p>",
